The strikethrough indicates a deprecation, meaning the function still works but will be removed in a future release. Don’t worry too much about it now.

It is likely your motor controller library has introduced a configuration API that takes a multi-setting config object. This means that all the methods whose functionality the new API obviates, will be marked deprecated.

That looks like you may be using a Talon FX. In Phoenix 6, invert is a config, so setInverted() is blocking and should not be called periodically like that (call it once on robot construction). There are also some edge cases with it that make it a footgun (which is why we’re removing it), so we recommend setting the config instead along with all your other configs.

More information is available in the deprecation message (shown on hover).
